BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:rtI1kJT2Irg6efC0yOGeX
SUMMARY:My Dinner with SAM
DTSTAMP:20260326T215651Z
DTSTART:20260409T013000Z
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate the art of food at intimate chef dinners inspired by 
	SAM's three unique sites. Dine in artful and inspiring settings while enjo
	ying a dynamic evening with culinary artists\, local producers and makers\
	, and more. Stay tuned\, tickets to these limited-seating dinners will be 
	available in January. Dinner dates and venues Thursday\, March 12 6:30 pm 
	Guest chef: Preeti Agarwal\, Meesha and Kricket Club Seattle Asian Art Mus
	eum Wednesday\, April 8 6:30 pm Guest chef: Kevin Smith\, Beast & Cleaver\
	, Little Beast\, and The Peasant Seattle Art Museum May Olympic Sculpture 
	Park Guest chef & date to come My Dinner with SAM is a major fundraising e
	vent and all proceeds benefit SAM's education\, community engagement\, and
	 exhibition programs. 3-Dinner Series VIP Tickets $1\,250 per person One V
	IP ticket to each dinner Recognition as a series sponsor on all evening pr
	ograms and dedicated event emails Special take-away at each dinner Complim
	entary parking at Seattle Art Museum and Olympic Sculpture Park Individual
	 Dinner Tickets Benefactor - $550 per person One ticket to one dinner Reco
	gnition on evening program Special take-away at the dinner Complimentary p
	arking at Seattle Art Museum and Olympic Sculpture Park Patron - $350 per 
	person One ticket to one dinner All but $150 per dinner is tax-deductible.
	 If you are unable to attend the event\, please consider making a donation
	 to support My Dinner with SAM. To make a tax-deductible donation\, please
	 contact us at dinnerwithSAM@seattleartmuseum.org or 206.654.3123.\n\nhttp
	s://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/my-dinner-with-sam/17799815/2026
	-04-08T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Food & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/my-dinner-with-sam/177998
	15/2026-04-08T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-food
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Food & Drink
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H30M
END:VEVENT
